ZH: 我每天早上都会先刷牙再磨牙。
EN: Every morning, I brush my teeth before grinding them.

ZH: 这块石头经过二十年的磨砺，变得十分光滑。
EN: This stone has become very smooth after twenty years of grinding.

ZH: 他通过无数次失败的尝试磨炼出自己的技术。
EN: He sharpened his skills through countless failed attempts.

ZH: 这本书是作者多年来磨练出的心血结晶。
EN: This book is the culmination of years of hard work by the author.

ZH: 在困难的环境中磨炼自己的意志力是非常重要的。
EN: It is important to sharpen one's willpower in difficult environments.

ZH: 他从小就被家庭环境磨练得十分坚强。
EN: His family environment toughened him up from a young age.

ZH: 他不停地磨练自己的演讲技巧，终于成为了一名著名的演讲家。
EN: He kept honing his public speaking skills and eventually became a famous speaker.

ZH: 坚持每天做锻炼可以使身体更加强壮。
EN: Regular exercise can strengthen the body.

ZH: 只有经过磨练和坚持，才能取得成功。
EN: Success can only be achieved through hard work and perseverance.

ZH: 这个项目的成功需要团队成员之间的密切合作。
EN: The success of this project requires close cooperation between team members.

ZH: 他花费了数年的时间磨练出了自己的摄影技艺。
EN: He spent several years sharpening his photography skills.

ZH: 他的雕刻作品经过数月的磨砺，最终展现出非凡的艺术品质。
EN: His carving works, after months of grinding, finally show extraordinary artistic qualities.

ZH: 失利并没有让他丧失信心，反而更加坚定了他的决心。
EN: Failure did not discourage him, but instead strengthened his resolve.

ZH: 艺术家用心磨砺着自己的技艺，创作出了令人惊叹的作品。
EN: The artist hones his skills diligently and creates amazing works.

